                    <span>I picked up this book thinking I knew everything there is to know about the game of baseball, boy was I wrong!  I have learned so much from this book, I feel that if I told George Steinbrenner  that I read Tim McCarvers Baseball For Brain Surgeans and Other Fans, that he would hire me on the spot as manager and fire Torre. This book is that good. This book is also fun to read. You would't be able to enjoy this book if you do not know about baseball already, because it gets a little complex sometimes. So go out and get this book if you like baseball and want to learn more about how the game is played</span>
                  
              
